text: Camille Bonnet (31 August 1918 – 17 November 2020) was a French rugby union player. He won the 1944–45 French Rugby Union Championship. He was born in Nogaro, France. His career lasted from 1936 until 1948. Bonnet died of COVID-19 on 17 November 2020, at the age of 102. ==References== Category:1918 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in France Category:French rugby union players Category:French centenarians Category:People from Gers Category:Sportspeople from Occitanie
